docs.abstract: Democrats are campaigning to fix an issue that is already starting to resolve itself for many teachers and other public servants.
docs.snippet: Democrats are campaigning to fix an issue that is already starting to resolve itself for many teachers and other public servants.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Bernie Sanders recently announced a $1.6 trillion plan to forgive all student loans, he had a particular kind of borrower in mind. “You are not truly free when you cannot pursue your dream of becoming a teacher, environmentalist, journalist or nurse,” he said, “because you cannot make enough money to cover your monthly student loan payments.”

headline.main: It’s Easy to Forget, but a Program to Forgive Student Loans Already Exists
headline.print_headline: How the Student Loan Forgiveness Program Fell Short

docs.abstract: The ride-hailing company’s cuts follow an internal reorganization and questions about whether it can make money.
docs.snippet: The ride-hailing company’s cuts follow an internal reorganization and questions about whether it can make money.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber said it laid off a third of its marketing team on Monday, or about 400 people, as the ride-hailing company tries to cut costs and streamline its operations after its initial public offering in May.

headline.main: Uber Lays Off 400 as Profitability Doubts Linger After I.P.O.
headline.print_headline: Uber Cuts 400 From Marketing as Profitability Doubts Persist After a Weak I.P.O.

docs.abstract: Negotiators left Shanghai on Wednesday with little immediate sign of progress as both sides appear to be settling in for a long economic clash.
docs.snippet: Negotiators left Shanghai on Wednesday with little immediate sign of progress as both sides appear to be settling in for a long economic clash.
docs.lead_paragraph: American and Chinese negotiators finished talks on Wednesday with little progress toward ending a trade war that has shaken the world’s economic confidence and rattled markets.

headline.main: U.S.-China Trade Talks End With No Deal in Sight
headline.print_headline: Rift Remains As Meetings With China Come to End

docs.abstract: A program with an intensive approach offers a rare success story in producing lasting wage gains. Its guiding principle: “We will not let them fail.”
docs.snippet: A program with an intensive approach offers a rare success story in producing lasting wage gains. Its guiding principle: “We will not let them fail.”
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN ANTONIO — The economic odds facing Avigail Rodriguez a few years ago couldn’t have been much worse. An undocumented immigrant and a single mother, she lived in a cramped apartment in a tough neighborhood in San Antonio and earned just $9 an hour working as a nurse’s assistant.

headline.main: Job Training Can Change Lives. See How San Antonio Does It.
headline.print_headline: Job Training Is a New Shot At Prosperity For Texans

docs.abstract: Charitable organizations can find themselves targets of protests caused by the actions of their benefactors.
docs.snippet: Charitable organizations can find themselves targets of protests caused by the actions of their benefactors.
docs.lead_paragraph: Not so long ago, philanthropy was an area where politics were left at the door. Conservatives and liberals on a philanthropic board could agree to disagree behind closed doors, but the public paid little attention as hospitals, cultural institutions and universities expanded thanks to gifts from the wealthy.

headline.main: As Politics Creep Into Philanthropy, Beneficiaries Come Under Fire
headline.print_headline: When a Donor Is a Blessing and a Bull’s-Eye

docs.abstract: Clashes at one of the world’s busiest transportation hubs could cast further doubt on the city’s future as a business capital on China’s doorstep.
docs.snippet: Clashes at one of the world’s busiest transportation hubs could cast further doubt on the city’s future as a business capital on China’s doorstep.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Violence and disarray at Hong Kong’s airport have cast a fresh shadow over the territory’s status as a global financial and business capital.

headline.main: Hong Kong’s Economy Shudders After Protests Plunge Airport Into Chaos
headline.print_headline: Economy Trembles  Across Hong Kong  After Airport Chaos

docs.abstract: White House advisers discount warnings of a possible recession. But the president may be gambling that the Federal Reserve can ward off that prospect.
docs.snippet: White House advisers discount warnings of a possible recession. But the president may be gambling that the Federal Reserve can ward off that prospect.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Against the backdrop of mounting evidence that the global economy is weakening, President Trump is caught between his desire to pursue the trade war with China he promised to win and his need to keep the economy humming as the 2020 election approaches.

headline.main: Economic Trouble Signs Hang Over Trump’s Trade War
headline.print_headline: Trade Warrior On Risky Path For Economy
